The paper discusses the localization of nodes in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) in computer science. The use of multidimensional scaling (MDS) technique and heuristic method for distance calculation suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (LG) and systems and control (SY). The paper also involves simulations and evaluation, which could be related to data structures (DS) and information theory (IT).
